From Dan Sorenson Subject Re WACO burning writes Can you imagine what happens when a magazine explodes Generally the ship sinks sorry there's a picture of the USS Iowa next to my desk Bullets go flying every IMHO these gunshot wounds were actually caused when the magazines went First unless that round is chambered there is little threat of penetration by the bullet or the brass for that Unless that expanding gas is held in an enclosed space you get a nice pop and not enough threat for even firefighters to worry Finally it's rather simple to tell if a person was shot prior to being burned to a See by the time the ammunition went up those people were quite Look for blood around the wound particularly However it's my contention that it makes little difference whether they died from exploding ammunition or fire the Feds seem to have shared responsibility for Dan Sorenson DoD ISU only censors what I read not what I Don't blame USENET Post to exotic distant Meet exciting unusual And flame